did.abstract: These records were generated by the Office of the VP for Enrollment from 1993 to 2005. The office oversees the Office of Admissions, Enrollment Operations and Student Financial Services. The record types include statistics, policies and procedures, planning and management studies, and general information.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office of Enrollment oversees the offices of admission, enrollment operations and student financial services at Rice University.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains records reflecting the daily business of the Rice University Office of Enrollment, including expense reports for faculty travel and for department spending, application records from potential faculty and graduate students, and documentation on incoming students.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This material is restricted for privacy reasons. Permission to access the material must be granted in writing from the Office of the Vice President for Enrollment.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Stored off-site at the Library Service Center. Please contact the Woodson Research Center for more information: woodson@rice.edu or call 713-348-2586.
